About

It’s the little things that make a big difference

I aspire to be a part of projects whose complexity defies the spirit of an engineer. Seeking creative and challenging tasks, to work in a motivated team of committed and enthusiastic colleagues. Friendly and open nature, driven, creative, with a motivated approach to tasks with pro activity as a worker and human being.

Hobbies & Activities

Favorite Books

Inspiried

Marty Cagan draws a blueprint from top tech companies, for building products that truly resonate with what users are looking for, breaking down the principles of effective product management, highlighting the importance of customer-centric design and agile team collaboration.

Leaders Make the Future

Bob Johansen explores how forward-thinking leadership can thrive amongst rapid change. By expecting trends up to ten years ahead—far beyond the typical quarterly mindset—Johansen does a deep dive into valuable insights for shaping resilient, innovative teams.

The New Human Capital Strategy

This book is all about redefining the way organizations should think about talent management, focusing on the strategic role of human capital in driving business success. By aligning workforce development with company goals, the teams behind the work are the key competitive advantage.
